Text.Value: The cleric who cast the Sending was wounded. Should I have sobbed on her shoulder?
When surrounded by the enemy, every word counts. Be grateful she sent anything at all.
We're all going to die.
Now if there's more to discuss, then bloody well come in. And wipe your boots.

EditorData.NodeContext: Moving on from the conflict immediately - she has better things to do.

Text.Value: So old.

EditorData.NodeContext: Chiming up, enjoying this bullying of Jaheira

Text.Value: And you were supposed to be dead. That's what your oh-so-stoic message meant, yes?

EditorData.NodeContext: 'So what?' Not to be diverted by Jaheira's excuses

Text.Value: This is a beautiful home. I figured Jaheira lived in a cave. Alone.
Not in this lifetime.
If you are trying to help me, please stop.
You are a very irritating girl.
Cast a glance at Minsc.
Ah-ah. This isn't your house, remember? You'll keep a civil tongue under our roof, if we let you stay at all.

EditorData.NodeContext: Chiding. Not serious about not letting Jaheira stay, but forcing her to go through the motions of being judged anyway

Text.Value: Fine. Better in our home than quivering in some bush out in the Cloakwood.

EditorData.NodeContext: Shrug, not fazed

Text.Value: I got my skin saved by this one. We've come to take the fight to the cult - which is exactly why you all cannot be here.
See, mother? A little positivity.

EditorData.NodeContext: Back to Jaheira: 'You should be more like this one'

Text.Value: The message went: 'I'm sorry. You know what to do.'

EditorData.NodeContext: turning back to Jaheira, deadpan and unimpressed

Text.Value: Seems I'm out-voted. See, mother - that is how you go about talking things through with your family.

EditorData.NodeContext: Sighing, relenting - but getting one last pointed dig in at Jaheira.

Text.Value: Enough, Rion. I taught you better manners than that.
Yet here you are. So - what happened out there?
So fight. That's what all you heroes and Harpers are for, isn't it?

EditorData.NodeContext: Shrug - there's a job to be done, so do it

Text.Value: She can stay - but only if she brought home presents.

EditorData.NodeContext: Sober judgement

Text.Value: Hah - now there is a phrase Jaheira has never uttered. But no.

EditorData.NodeContext: Mildly derisive

Text.Value: Oh, Malar's mark. Here we go.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: We enter the hallway to find the little girl has run to a young half-elf and half-orc. They listen to her a moment, then stand to glare at the party; specifically, JAHEIRA.
EditorData.InternalNodeContext: The granddaughter has spotted Jaheira and reported she's coming, ahead of time.

Text.Value: The cult is powerful - it's not going to be an easy fight.
Why? You plan on winning, don't you?

EditorData.NodeContext: Brushing off Jaheira's warnings about the coming danger

Text.Value: You should really just listen to your mother.
Some battles, even Boo is not brave enough to fight.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Shaking his head, urging us not to get involved.

Text.Value: Only seven? That's cold, Jaheira.
Smells it, too.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Looking at Jaheira, speaking to Rion

Text.Value: Rion -
She wasn't exactly willing. I think she'd rather go back to the shadow-curse.
Forgive us, mother. We're just surprised you still know how to find your way home.

EditorData.NodeContext: Shrugging, snarky - 'you can hardly blame us for being confused'.

Text.Value: What did she say?

You're the one who saved her, so tell me - are we all doomed?

EditorData.NodeContext: 'Well - what about you?'

Text.Value: This really isn't any of my business.
Are we quite sure she hasn't actually died this time, brother? She looks dead.

EditorData.NodeContext: Mock curiousity - speaking to her brother as if Jaheira isn't there. Looking her up and down and not impressed with what she sees.

EditorData.NodeContext: Snort, approving

Ugh. The one stern parent is quite enough, thank you very much.

EditorData.NodeContext: Scoffing at our tone

Text.Value: Mother? Jaheira, these are your children?
She always brings the smartest people home, too.

EditorData.NodeContext: Snort, mocking (not mean, just unimpressed)

Text.Value: Oh, Malar's mark. An ambush.

EditorData.NodeContext: Bluntly steam-rolling over Jaheira, speaking directly to player: 'did you hear what this shit-head did?'

Text.Value: (No you didn't.)
What a surprise.

EditorData.NodeContext: Deadpan, sarcastic - your mother Jaheira has finally deigned to turn up at your home

Synopsis: Jaheira is reunited with her family, who thought her missing out in the shadowlands. Her eldest daughter Rion takes the lead, quizzing Jaheira on how she got back to the city and her silence since then.
